doctype html
html(lang='en-us')
  head
    meta(charset='utf-8')
    meta(http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible', content='IE=edge,chrome=1')
    meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width')
    link(rel="stylesheet" type = "text/css", href = "../jquery-ui/themes/base/jquery-ui.min.css")
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css')
    link(href='https://cdn.bootcss.com/twitter-bootstrap/3.4.0/css/bootstrap.min.css', rel='stylesheet')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='../bootstrap-star-rating/css/star-rating.min.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='css/style.css')
  body        
    #container
      .context
        #likedphones
            h5(style="text-align:center; font-weight:bold; background:yellow") Task: Find 5 phones you want to put in your shopping cart.
            p Please rate your liked phones in terms of its&nbsp
              strong pleasant surprise.
            ul.list-group
        #task1(style="display:none") You have finished the task, please fill the final questionnaire.

        br
        button.btn.btn-info#questionnaire-1(style="display:none") Please fill the final questionnaire :)
        br
        button#start-task.btn.btn-primary Start study

      .iphone-x
        .loading
        .window(style="display:none")
          .chat
        input#message(type='text', name='message', value='', placeholder="Chat with me!", style="display:none")
      .task
        #accordion
          h3 Tips for tuning the recommendations by phone features
          div
            p.desc Currently the system supports searching by 5 phone features,
            br

            p.desc
              span.exp(data-container="body" data-toggle='popover', data-placement='auto', data-content='Energy represents a perceptual measure of intensity and activity. Typically, energetic tracks feel fast, loud, and noisy. For example, death metal has high energy, while a Bach prelude scores low on the scale.', style="color:#2061E5") Energy:
              span To tweak recommendation by price, you can say
            p.example "I want to buy a cheaper phone."
            p.example "The price can be higher."
            br
            
            p.desc
              span.exp(data-container="body" data-toggle='popover', data-placement='auto', data-content='Danceability describes how suitable a track is for dancing based on a combination of musical elements including tempo, rhythm stability, beat strength, and overall regularity.', style="color:#2061E5") Danceability:
              span To tweak recommendation by resolution, you can say
            p.example "I need a phone having better display"
            br

            p.desc
              span.exp(data-container="body" data-toggle='popover', data-placement='auto', data-content='Speechiness detects the presence of spoken words in a track.', style="color:#2061E5") Speechiness:
              span To tweak recommendation by memory, you can say
            p.example "I need a phone with a large storage"
            p.example "I need a phone having more space for saving my photos"
            br

            p.desc
              span.exp(data-container="body" data-toggle='popover', data-placement='auto', data-content='Tempo is the speed or pace of a given piece and derives directly from the average beat duration.', style="color:#2061E5") Tempo:
              span To tweak recommendation by computing performance, you can say
            p.example "I want to buy a phone having larger RAM"
            p.example "I want to buy a phone having better GPU"
            p.example "I want to buy a phone running applications faster"
            br

            p.desc
              span.exp(data-container="body" data-toggle='popover', data-placement='auto', data-content='Tracks with high valence sound more positive (e.g. happy, cheerful, euphoric), while tracks with low valence sound more negative (e.g. sad, depressed, angry).', style="color:#2061E5") Valence:
              span To tweak recommendation by barnd, you can say
            p.example "I like iPhone"
            p.example "I want to buy Huawei mobile phones"

          h3 Tips for tuning the recommendations by phone operating system (OS)
          div
            p.desc
              | If you want to search for phones by OS
              | you can say
            br
            p.example "I want to buy an Android phone"
            p.example "I like iPhone"

          h3 Tips for tuning the recommendations by size
          div
            p.desc If you want to search for phones by size, you can say
            br
            p.example "I like light weight phone"
            p.example "I want to buy a phone with slim body"
